ethods we used have become part of the global knowledge of the detector community in high energy physics. The very high level of performances achieved make the researched devices suitable to a range of applications outside high energy physics.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>9682B746-8E35-4B5A-A442-93DBFECFA5A3</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>546081be1c0790.62504009</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Aerospace, Defence and Marine,Electronics,Energy,Healthcare,Security and Diplomacy</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs><gtr:policyInfluenceOutput><gtr:areas/><gtr:description>Improved tools for science (HEP)</gtr:description><gtr:geographicReach>Asia</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>4FDFCDD2-24DA-4102-B76B-EEC19C106F68</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>54608b45a27965.37045665</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:type>Influenced training of practitioners or researchers</gtr:type></gtr:policyInfluenceOutput></gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>9F80400A-5B54-4FF7-84D0-4990746CAD6C</gtr:id><gtr:title>Results with p-type pixel sensors with different geometries for the HL-LHC</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Nuclear Instruments and Methods in Physics Research Section A: Accelerators, Spectrometers, Detectors and Associated Equipment</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/faf8bded6f7e4ad7f6515968a6939e0c"><gtr:id>faf8bded6f7e4ad7f6515968a6939e0c</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Allport P</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2013-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:outcomeId>dgBgu79HW4B</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>889FE8FB-7908-4ACC-8A26-B47C9FDE99D8</gtr:id><gtr:title>Degradation of charge sharing after neutron irradiation in strip silicon detectors with different geometr